                            <comment id="12769271" author="streamy" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 15:55:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 across the board.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would say that one advantage of documentation vs an automated tool is that it provides a good opportunity for someone to learn what decisions are being made according to different hardware/cluster specs (rather than a magic black box).  Many users start out on 1 or 5 nodes with plans to move to 10, 20, or more.  As we build up a good repository of information, we can add more as we/users learn.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another major factor is what the expected load patterns are, especially related to where you might host your ZK nodes, max number of map/reduce tasks, etc...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14064176" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2014 21:54:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Five years hence, doubtful if it will happen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
